Ri was referring to a joint statement by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first ever meeting between the current US president and the North Korean leader in Singapore on June 12, when Kim pledged to work on the "denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula", while Trump guaranteed North Korea's security.
North Korea wants to formally end the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States has made it a condition that Pyongyang give up its nuclear weapons before that.
Washington has also ignored calls for easing tough international sanctions on North Korea.
