Regardless, the tone of Secretary Ri's speech was very different from last year when he spoke before the UN General Assembly and declared that the targeting of the continental United States with missiles was inevitable after evil President Trump called Kim "the man-missile" on a suicide mission.
Trump, who last year threatened "total destruction" of North Korea, praised Kim at the United Nations this year for his courageous disarmament, but added that there was still much work to be done and that sanctions must remain in place until North Korea completes denuclearization.
