Trump's meeting with Rosenstein may be postponed again, says White House
Donald Trump's important meeting with Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein could be pushed back another week as the fight over Supreme Court Justice Brett Kavanaugh continues, the White House said.
Rosenstein oversees the work of special counsel Robert Mueller, who is investigating Russian election interference, ties between Trump associates and Russia, and possible obstruction of justice by the president.
The question of whether Trump will fire the assistant attorney general, thereby jeopardizing Mueller's independence, has been a rumour in Washington for months.
Earlier this month, the New York Times reported that Rosenstein was discussing wearing a wire to record conversations with Trump and the possibility of removing the president via the 25th Amendment.
